## Description {#details}

A CRTP base for tables that are built on demand, e.g.

Global Offset Tables and Procedure <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/jitlink/#abee99c9c75d23a0304e5e58e3128a55f">Linkage</a> Tables. The getEntyrForTarget function returns the table entry corresponding to the given target, calling down to the implementation class to build an entry if one does not already exist.

### registerPreExistingEntry() {#ace7f4ad413507742c3a483f951e357cf}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;typename TableManagerImplT&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>bool llvm::jitlink::TableManager&lt; TableManagerImplT &gt;::registerPreExistingEntry (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/jitlink/symbol">Symbol</a> &amp; Target, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/jitlink/symbol">Symbol</a> &amp; Entry)</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/register">Register</a> a pre-existing entry.

Objects may include pre-existing table entries (e.g. for GOTs). This method can be used to register those entries so that they will not be duplicated by createEntry the first time that getEntryForTarget is called.
